  m_Name: Ballroom Relic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Tureens
  description: 'Tureens were large serving dishes used for soups, stews, and other
    shared meals during formal dinners. In wealthy households, they were often made
    from porcelain or silver and decorated to match the dining service. They played
    an important role in formal dining, where meals were served in multiple courses. '
